4. Warranty, mailware, copyright, copying


4.1 Warranty

There is no warranty, neither for correct program functions nor
for any damages caused by TextConv.


4.2 Mailware

Since version 1.50, TextConv is a MAILWARE-program.
The principles for MAILWARE are the same as for FREEWARE, that means,
the usage of the program and the spreading is free.
If you like the program and you use it regulary, you should send @{"me" LINK "Author"}
an e-mail, a (picture) postcard or a letter. There you can tell me
if you like the program or what you liked to have changed.
So you can help me to find bugs and improve future versions of
TextConv.


4.3 Copyright, copying

All rights are restricted to the @{"author" LINK "Author"}.
©1995-97 SciTech SD.
©1995-97 Alexander Haas

This program may be copied and spreaded as you like, but no fee
may be charged in any form, except a suitable fee for copying,
but max. the price of a DD-disk (20ATS/3DM/2US$) or, with printed
manual, 50ATS/7DM/5US$.

TextConv consists of the following archives:
 - textconv151d.lha:
      German version of TextConv V1.51
      Contains the program, conversion tables, dockbrushes,
      Documentation in ASCII- and Amigaguide-format
 - textconv151e.lha
